-- Nynas Gets 750 Million Euros in Loans for Takeover, Refinancing
-- B y   S t e p h e n   M o r r i s
-- 2012-01-11T13:39:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/nynas-gets-750-million-euros-in-loans-for-takeover-refinancing.html
Nynas AB (NYNA) , a venture between Neste
Oil Oyj and  Petroleos de Venezuela , got 750 million euros ($952
million) in loans to fund the acquisition of Royal Dutch Shell
Plcâ€™s Harburg refinery and to refinance existing debt.  The five-year facility includes a 575 million-euro term
loan backing the acquisition of the Hamburg-based refinery, a
125 million-euro revolving credit and a 50 million-euro letter
of credit to refinance debt, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  Svenska Handelsbanken AB and SEB AG coordinated the loans,
and were joined by Danske Bank A/S, DNB NOR Bank ASA, BNP
Paribas Fortis and Nordea Bank AB in syndicating the financing,
according to an e-mailed statement from the Stockholm-based
company today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
